## Summary

This pull request addresses issue #1660, which identified that the 'RepoCreate' class was mutable, particularly through the 'with' method. This PR modifies the 'RepoCreate' class to make it immutable, thereby improving thread-safety and aligning with best practices.

## Changes

1. A new constructor parameter called 'otherMap' is introduced to pass additional JSON key-value pairs.
2. The 'with' method for the 'RepoCreate' class has been made immutable. Instead of modifying the internal 'other' map, it returns a new 'RepoCreate' object with the updated map.
3. All the existing methods that return modified 'RepoCreate' objects (like 'withName', 'withPrivacy', etc.) are updated to include 'otherMap'.

